{
  "texts": [
    "Children imitate their parents in their practical life.",
    "Brown (1994) argued that parents shaped their children's attitudes and other aspects of their lives early on, which in turn shaped their future perspectives.",
    "The society and community where the learner lives shape the psyche and personality of the learners in many subtle ways.",
    "The attitudes and perceptions embedded in a community\"s social life essentially become a part of the learner\"s psychology.",
    "If a community's attitudes toward English and its culture are positive, the learner will surely hold positive ways."
  ]
}